trailingComments.value: * * Pick an element from range(start, stop, step) uniformly at random. * * Return an element from range(start, stop, step) selected uniformly at random. * If step is positive, this set corresponds to * {x: x in [start, stop[ AND x % step = 0}. * If step is negative, the range has to be given in reverse order, that is, * largest value first, smallest value second. Both the starting value and the * step value are optional. By default the starting value is 0. * The default for the step value is 1. * * TODO: Handle empty ranges. * * @param {number} [start=0] - The starting value. * @param {number} stop - The stopping value. * @param {number} [step=1] - The step value. * @return {number} The picked element.
